  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign covering inlet velocity, fluid viscosity, and impeller geometry tolerances was executed as part of the validation activities; results are summarised in the validation report and informed the acceptance rationale. The UQ campaign demonstrated that model predictions remain within the RH < 1 acceptance band across the sampled parameter space.",
