      "description": "CFD predictions of normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA experimental data for five flow-speed operating points. All predictions within 15% of measured NIH values; RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all points. Mesh convergence confirmed at GCI < 2% on NIH. The UQ campaign (Latin hypercube, n=128 samples) covering ±5% impeller tip clearance, ±3% inlet velocity, and ±4% blood viscosity showed 99th-percentile RH = 0.94, confirming robustness of the acceptance conclusion.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Normalised index of hemolysis (NIH); relative hemolysis index (RH)",
      "acceptanceCriterion": "RH < 1.0 at all five operating points",
